"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-news-paris-ap-international-olympic-committee-france-olympians-b2528941.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 321, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  InParis' outskirts, a bright-eyed young girl is eager for the Olympic and Paralympic Games to end.\", \"from\": 322, \"to\": 444, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's because the swimming club where 10-year-old Lyla Kebbi trains will inherit an Olympic pool.\", \"from\": 446, \"to\": 544, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 497, \"end\": 501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyla_Garrity\", \"score\": 0.9999999986539478, \"rank\": 1.3463894000618613e-09, \"text\": \"Lyla\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyla_Garrity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyla_Garrity\"}, {\"begin\": 502, \"end\": 507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kebbi_State\", \"score\": 0.9999999979499989, \"rank\": 2.0499973405704013e-09, \"text\": \"Kebbi\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kebbi_State\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kebbi_State\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will be dismantled after the Games and trucked from the Olympic race venue in Paris' high-rise business district to Sevran, a Paris-area town with less glitter and wealth.\", \"from\": 545, \"to\": 719, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 626, \"end\": 631, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3770163784666136e-30, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 664, \"end\": 670, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sevran\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sevran\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sevran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sevran\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There, the pieces will be bolted back together and - voila !\", \"from\": 720, \"to\": 780, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"- Kebbi and her swim team will have a new Olympic-sized pool to splash around in.\", \"from\": 781, \"to\": 862, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's incredible !\\\"\", \"from\": 864, \"to\": 883, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"she says.\", \"from\": 884, \"to\": 893, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I hope it's going to bring us luck,\\\" adds her mother, Nora.\", \"from\": 894, \"to\": 954, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 949, \"end\": 953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_The_Flash_characters\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 1.3060219036593802e-12, \"text\": \"Nora\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_The_Flash_characters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_The_Flash_characters\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 100 days as of Wednesday, the Paris Olympics will kick off with a wildly ambitious waterborne opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 956, \"to\": 1070, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But the first Games in a century in France's capital will not be judged for spectacle alone.\", \"from\": 1071, \"to\": 1163, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1107, \"end\": 1113, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999926321834, \"rank\": 7.315645819941514e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another yardstick will be their impact on disadvantaged Paris suburbs, away from the city-center landmarks that are hosting much of the action.\", \"from\": 1164, \"to\": 1307, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1220, \"end\": 1225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3770163784666136e-30, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By promising socially positive and also less polluting and less wasteful Olympics, the city synonymous with romance is also setting itself the high bar of making future Games generally more desirable.\", \"from\": 1309, \"to\": 1509, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Critics question their value for a world grappling with climate warming and other emergencies.\", \"from\": 1511, \"to\": 1605, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Potential host cities became so Games-averse that Paris and Los Angeles were the only remaining candidates in 2017 when theInternational Olympic Committeeselected them for 2024 and 2028, respectively.\", \"from\": 1606, \"to\": 1806, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1656, \"end\": 1661, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3770163784666136e-30, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1666, \"end\": 1677, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.1022937469770596e-16, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After scandals and the $13 billion cost of the pandemic-delayed Tokyo Games in 2021, unfulfilled promises of beneficial change for host Rio de Janeiro in 2016 and the 2014 Winter Games in Sochi tarnished by Russian doping and President Vladimir Putin's subsequent land grabs in Ukraine, the Switzerland-based IOC has mountains of skepticism to dispel.\", \"from\": 1808, \"to\": 2159, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1944, \"end\": 1958, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.472643273474076e-28, \"text\": \"Rio de Janeiro\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}, {\"begin\": 1996, \"end\": 2001, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sochi\", \"score\": 0.9999632268031159, \"rank\": 3.67745487556966e-05, \"text\": \"Sochi\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sochi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sochi\"}, {\"begin\": 2015, \"end\": 2022, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999335018284289, \"rank\": 3.471597197442729e-05, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 2044, \"end\": 2058, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.518877009550596e-37, \"text\": \"Vladimir Putin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\"}, {\"begin\": 2086, \"end\": 2093, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999999995116013, \"rank\": 2.73491512819448e-10, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 2117, \"end\": 2120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.028681140066494e-40, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Virtuous Summer Games in Paris could help the long-term survival of the IOC's mega-event.\", \"from\": 2161, \"to\": 2250, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2170, \"end\": 2182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3395931395937881e-13, \"text\": \"Summer Games\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 2186, \"end\": 2191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3770163784666136e-30, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2233, \"end\": 2236, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.028681140066494e-40, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"SPREADING BENEFITS BEYOND CENTRAL PARIS  The idea that the July 26-Aug. 11 Games and Aug. 28-Sept. 8 Paralympics should benefit disadvantaged communities in the Seine-Saint-Denis region northeast of Paris was built from the outset into the city's plans.\", \"from\": 2252, \"to\": 2505, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2451, \"end\": 2456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3770163784666136e-30, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Seine-Saint-Denis is mainland France's poorest region.\", \"from\": 2507, \"to\": 2561, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2507, \"end\": 2524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\"}, {\"begin\": 2537, \"end\": 2543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999926321834, \"rank\": 7.315645819941514e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thanks to generations of immigration, it also is vibrantly diverse, counting 130 nationalities and more than 170 languages spoken by its 1.6 million inhabitants.\", \"from\": 2562, \"to\": 2723, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For Seine-Saint-Denis kids facing racial discrimination and other barriers, sports are sometimes a route out.\", \"from\": 2724, \"to\": 2833, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2728, \"end\": 2745, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"World Cup winner Kylian Mbapp\\u00e9 honed his silky soccer skills as a boy in the Seine-Saint-Denis town of Bondy.\", \"from\": 2834, \"to\": 2943, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2851, \"end\": 2864, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kylian_Mbapp\\u00e9\", \"score\": 0.999999999231477, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kylian Mbapp\\u00e9\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kylian_Mbapp\\u00e9\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kylian_Mbapp\\u00e9\"}, {\"begin\": 2937, \"end\": 2942, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bondy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9913381445130196e-42, \"text\": \"Bondy\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bondy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bondy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Once heavily industrialized, Seine-Saint-Denis became grim and scary in parts after many jobs were lost.\", \"from\": 2945, \"to\": 3049, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2974, \"end\": 2991, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rioting rocked its streets in 2005 and again last year.\", \"from\": 3050, \"to\": 3105, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Members of an Islamic extremist cell that killed 130 people in the French capital in 2015 hid after the carnage in an apartment in the town of Saint-Denis and were killed in a shootout with heavily armed SWAT teams.\", \"from\": 3106, \"to\": 3321, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3120, \"end\": 3137, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_extremism\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Islamic extremist\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_extremism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_extremism\"}, {\"begin\": 3173, \"end\": 3179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9955766259582766, \"rank\": 0.004382918830905898, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3310, \"end\": 3314, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SWAT\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.399598221090445e-18, \"text\": \"SWAT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SWAT\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SWAT\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That drama unfolded just a 15-minute walk from the Olympic stadium that will host track and field and rugby and the closing ceremonies.\", \"from\": 3322, \"to\": 3457, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Concretely, the Games will leave a legacy of new and refurbished sports infrastructure in Seine-Saint-Denis, although critics say the investment still is not enough to catch it up with better equipped, more prosperous regions.\", \"from\": 3459, \"to\": 3685, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3549, \"end\": 3566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mamitiana Rabarijaona grew up close to the Olympic stadium, built originally for the 1998 soccer World Cup.\", \"from\": 3687, \"to\": 3794, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He says it did not provide much of a boost for Seine-Saint-Denis residents.\", \"from\": 3795, \"to\": 3870, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3842, \"end\": 3859, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He believes the Olympics will be \\\"a big party\\\" and he will be among 45,000 volunteers who will be helping.\", \"from\": 3871, \"to\": 3977, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But he is not expecting Olympic-related investments to magically erase Seine-Saint-Denis' many difficulties.\", \"from\": 3978, \"to\": 4086, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4049, \"end\": 4066, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's like lifting the carpet and brushing the dust underneath,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 4088, \"to\": 4161, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It does not make it go away.\\\"\", \"from\": 4162, \"to\": 4192, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Seine-Saint-Denis got the new Olympic village that will become housing and offices when the 10,500Olympiansand 4,400 Paralympians have left.\", \"from\": 4194, \"to\": 4334, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4194, \"end\": 4211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It also is home to the Games' only purpose-built competition venue, an aquatics center for diving, water polo and artistic swimming events.\", \"from\": 4335, \"to\": 4474, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Other competition venues already existed, were previously planned or will be temporary.\", \"from\": 4475, \"to\": 4562, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We really were driven by the ambition of sobriety and above all not to build sports facilities that are not needed and which will have no reason to exist after the Games,\\\" Marie Barsacq, the organizing committee's legacy director, said in an interview.\", \"from\": 4564, \"to\": 4817, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The hand-me-down 50-meter pool for Sevran will be a significant upgrade.\", \"from\": 4819, \"to\": 4891, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4854, \"end\": 4860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sevran\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sevran\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sevran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sevran\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Seine-Saint-Denis town of 51,000 people was whacked by factory closures in the 1990s.\", \"from\": 4892, \"to\": 4981, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Its existing 25-meter pool is nearly 50 years old.\", \"from\": 4982, \"to\": 5032, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Other Seine-Saint-Denis towns are also getting new or renovated pools - particularly welcome for the region's children, because only half of them can swim.\", \"from\": 5034, \"to\": 5189, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The ambition for these Olympic Games ... is that they benefit everyone and for the longest time possible,\\\" said Sevran Mayor St\\u00e9phane Blanchet.\", \"from\": 5191, \"to\": 5335, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5304, \"end\": 5310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sevran\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sevran\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sevran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sevran\"}, {\"begin\": 5311, \"end\": 5316, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mayor_of_London\", \"score\": 0.9999999812616809, \"rank\": 1.8721552160397405e-08, \"text\": \"Mayor\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mayor_of_London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mayor_of_London\"}, {\"begin\": 5326, \"end\": 5334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blanchet_(harpsichord_makers)\", \"score\": 0.5898373953986847, \"rank\": 0.4226190476192673, \"text\": \"Blanchet\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blanchet_(harpsichord_makers)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blanchet_(harpsichord_makers)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics, Blanchet said, can not \\\"carry on just passing though and then moving on without thinking about tomorrow.\\\"\", \"from\": 5336, \"to\": 5455, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5350, \"end\": 5358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blanchet_(harpsichord_makers)\", \"score\": 0.5898373953986847, \"rank\": 0.4226190476192673, \"text\": \"Blanchet\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blanchet_(harpsichord_makers)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blanchet_(harpsichord_makers)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PARIS' COSTS COMPARE FAVORABLY  At close to 9 billion euros ($9.7 billion), more than half from sponsors, ticket sales and other non-public funding, Paris' expenses so far are less than for the last three Summer Games in Tokyo, Rio and London in 2012.\", \"from\": 5457, \"to\": 5708, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5606, \"end\": 5611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3770163784666136e-30, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 5678, \"end\": 5683, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999936335, \"rank\": 6.337058924114551e-12, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 5685, \"end\": 5688, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.5539225492747011, \"rank\": 0.8053065384483848, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 5693, \"end\": 5699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999777019186, \"rank\": 2.2296976702169028e-08, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Including policing and transport costs, the portion of the bill for French taxpayers is likely to be around 3 billion euros ($3.25 billon),France's body for auditing public funds said in its most recent study in July.\", \"from\": 5710, \"to\": 5927, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5778, \"end\": 5784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9955766259582766, \"rank\": 0.004382918830905898, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Security remains a challenge for the city repeatedly hit by deadly extremist violence.\", \"from\": 5929, \"to\": 6015, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The government downsized ambitions to have 600,000 people lining the River Seine for the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 6016, \"to\": 6122, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6085, \"end\": 6096, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Citing the risk of attacks, it shelved a promise that anyone could apply for hundreds of thousands of free tickets.\", \"from\": 6123, \"to\": 6238, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, the 326,000 spectators will either be paying ticket-holders or have been invited.\", \"from\": 6239, \"to\": 6329, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Privacy advocates are critical of video surveillance technology being deployed to spot security threats.\", \"from\": 6331, \"to\": 6435, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Campaigners for the homeless are concerned that they will be swept off streets.\", \"from\": 6436, \"to\": 6515, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Many Parisians plan to leave, to avoid the disruptions or to rent their homes to the expected 15 million visitors.\", \"from\": 6516, \"to\": 6630, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With trade unions pushing for Olympic bonuses, strikes are also possible.\", \"from\": 6631, \"to\": 6704, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And all this against an inflammable backdrop of geopolitical crises including but not limited to the Israel-Hamas war and Russia's invasion of Ukraine.\", \"from\": 6706, \"to\": 6857, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6828, \"end\": 6834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 5.692781343256316e-12, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 6849, \"end\": 6856, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999999995116013, \"rank\": 2.73491512819448e-10, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As a consequence, the IOC is not allowing athletes from Russia and ally Belarus to parade with other Olympians at the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 6858, \"to\": 6993, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6880, \"end\": 6883, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.028681140066494e-40, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 6914, \"end\": 6920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 5.692781343256316e-12, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 6930, \"end\": 6937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1138218135296572e-15, \"text\": \"Belarus\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Still, Olympics fans expect big things of Paris.\", \"from\": 6995, \"to\": 7043, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7037, \"end\": 7042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3770163784666136e-30, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They include Ayaovi Atindehou, a 32-year-old trainee doctor from Togo studying in France.\", \"from\": 7044, \"to\": 7133, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7109, \"end\": 7113, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Togo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.624899386659058e-14, \"text\": \"Togo\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Togo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Togo\"}, {\"begin\": 7126, \"end\": 7132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999926321834, \"rank\": 7.315645819941514e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic volunteer believes the Games can bridge divisions, even if just temporarily.\", \"from\": 7134, \"to\": 7222, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The whole world without racial differences, ethnic differences, religious differences.\", \"from\": 7224, \"to\": 7311, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We will be all together, shouting, celebrating,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 7312, \"to\": 7369, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We need the Olympic Games.\\\"\", \"from\": 7370, \"to\": 7398, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"___  APOlympics coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/2024-paris-olympic-games  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 7400, \"to\": 7611, \"entities\": []}]}"